Visualize the count of categories in each variable¶

In [22]:
categorical_columns = preprocessed_data_cat.drop(['posting_date'],axis=1)
column_names = list(categorical_columns.columns)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(8, 2, figsize=(20, 60))
for variable, subplot in zip(column_names, ax.flatten()):
    sns.countplot(categorical_columns[variable], ax=subplot, order = categorical_columns[variable].value_counts().index)
    for label in subplot.get_xticklabels():
        label.set_rotation(90)
